 Heritage Auctions offered the gray jacket and skirt , featuring a black zigzag applique , plus more than 150 other items from the Academy Award-winning film at auction on Saturday in Beverly Hills , California .
The dress - a jacket and full skirt ensemble was worn in the 1939 movie , including when Scarlett O'Hara encounters Rhett Butler , and when she gets attacked in the film .
It was one of 150 items that were part of the private collection of James Tumblin .